.TH "__tipc_bind" 9 "__tipc_bind" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__tipc_bind \- associate or disassocate TIPC name(s) with a socket
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __tipc_bind
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr *skaddr "  ","
.BI "int alen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
socket structure
.IP "skaddr" 12
socket address describing name(s) and desired operation
.IP "alen" 12
size of socket address data structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Name and name sequence binding is indicated using a positive scope value;
a negative scope value unbinds the specified name.  Specifying no name
(i.e. a socket address length of 0) unbinds all names from the socket.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, errno otherwise
.SH "NOTE"
This routine doesn't need to take the socket lock since it doesn't
access any non-constant socket information.
